-dog-licking-glass-isolated-260nw-2510152829.webp", "date_of_birth": "1996-02-19", "biography": "She is a Spanish teacher from Bogotá, Colombia, with over eight years of experience teaching both children and adults. Throughout her career, she has developed a strong passion for making language learning accessible, engaging, and culturally meaningful. She specializes in creating practical and creative learning materials designed especially for bilingual families, helping parents confidently teach Spanish to their children at home. Her approach combines structured language instruction with interactive activities that encourage natural communication and cultural connection. Known for her patience and adaptability, she has successfully supported learners of different ages and levels, fostering not only language skills but also a deeper appreciation for Hispanic culture.", "country_of_birth": "CO", "country_of_residence": "NO", "courses": [1, 2]}}, {"model": "spanishapp.status", "pk": 1, "fields": {"title": "Pending"}}, {"model": "spanishapp.status", "pk": 2, "fields": {"title": "Confirmed"}}, {"model": "spanishapp.status", "pk": 3, "fields": {"title": "Cancelled"}}, {"model": "spanishapp.status", "pk": 4, "fields": {"title": "Completed"}}]
